criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Have an approved indication for implantation of an CRT device (ESC guidelines ,
             including any update);

          -  Have a stable pharmacological therapy.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Have a contra-indication to general anesthesia;

          -  Have a scheduled cardiac surgery;

          -  Have had a recent myocardial infarction, unstable angina or cardiac revascularization
             (PTCA or CABG) within 1 month of enrollment;

          -  Have a life expectancy of less than 6 months;

          -  Are unable to provide informed consent;

          -  Are unable to comply with the follow-up schedule and tests;

          -  Are minor (age below 18 years);

          -  Are pregnant or are planning for pregnancy in the next 6 months.
